<%#
  views/partials/promo-strip.ejs

  What:  Eye-catching promo band that sits just under the header on every
         page. Highlights the welcome offer for new customers, matches the
         Zomato/Swiggy/Foodhub convention of surfacing the headline deal
         immediately on landing.
  Why:   First thing a new visitor sees after the location chip. Drives
         the "first order" hook without pushing sign-up in their face.
  Used:  Included from views/_layout.ejs right after the header.

  Static copy for now. Wire to /api/v1/promotions in the next phase so
  the strip swaps between active promos automatically.
-%>
<%#
  "Order now" button behaviour
  ────────────────────────────
  • No location yet  → opens the location modal so the user can pick
                       a delivery area first. Same as the header chip.
  • Location set     → goes straight to the home page (a plain <a href="/">).
                       Per the user request: don't ask for location
                       again — they already picked one. We point at "/"
                       (the restaurant feed) which is where they were
                       going to anyway, and the browser does a normal
                       full reload of the page.
-%>
<div class="promo-strip" role="region" aria-label="Welcome offer">
    <div class="promo-strip__inner">
        <span class="promo-strip__icon" aria-hidden="true">🎉</span>
        <p class="promo-strip__copy">
            <strong>50% OFF</strong>
            on your first order — use code
            <span class="promo-strip__code">WELCOME50</span>
        </p>
        <% if (user_location) { %>
            <a href="/" class="promo-strip__cta">Order now</a>
        <% } else { %>
            <button
                type="button"
                class="promo-strip__cta"
                data-action="open-location-modal"
            >
                Order now
            </button>
        <% } %>
    </div>
</div>
